#subtitle: Can the Center Party move beyond the Catholics?

= Building a Christian Party

Formed during the time of Bismarck, the Center Party was able to fight back the oppressive policies of the Kulterkampf and defended the rights of German Catholics.
However, with only the support of Catholics, the Center Party will not be able to get out of its perpetual minority position. As such, some in the party have talked about "leaving the tower" to appeal to the broader Protestant electorate. 

